import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['normal'])]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='normal', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Normal Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal temperatures?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_numeric(data['actual'], errors='coerce')
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data[['actual', 'normal']], ax=ax, palette='Set2')
    ax.set_xlabel('Temperature')
    ax.set_ylabel('Type')
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Actual', 'Normal'])
    plt.title('How does the distribution of actual temperatures compare to the normal temperatures?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecast'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by=['day'])
    sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(15,10)})
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='actual', data=data, label='Actual Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='normal', data=data, label='Normal Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='forecast', y='actual', data=data, label='Forecasted Temperature')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('How accurate are the weather forecasts compared to the actual temperatures recorded?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
